parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission shifting issues can cause the vehicle to become stuck in park or neutral, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially in situations where the vehicle is in motion or in a hazardous location.
symptoms: The vehicle refuses to shift into gear
including reverse or drive
the gearshift button is stuck
the vehicle is stuck in park or neutral
the ABS light comes on
and the vehicle may roll or move unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch assembly can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear or unable to shift, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially in situations where the vehicle is in motion or in a hazardous location.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the polycarbonate roof panel can cause it to crack or shatter, potentially falling on occupants or exploding outward onto following traffic, leading to accidents or injuries.

loss of physical strength properties
and ultimate failure of the roof panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of the service flap (hood) can cause it to fly off while driving, potentially causing a severe safety hazard, panic, and accidents.
